What is a Helm Repository?

A Helm Repository is like an App Store for Kubernetes.

Instead of downloading applications manually, you install them using Helm.

Examples:

NGINX
Prometheus
Grafana
Jenkins
Argo CD
PostgreSQL
Redis
Elasticsearc

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Helm Repository
      ↓
Stores Helm Charts

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Popular Helm Repositories

Repository			Purpose
Bitnami				General applications (NGINX, MySQL, Redis, PostgreSQL, Jenkins)
Prometheus Community		Prometheus, Alertmanager, kube-prometheus-stack
Grafana				Grafana, Loki, Tempo
Argo				Argo CD, Argo Workflows
Elastic				Elasticsearch, Kibana
Jetstack			cert-manager
ingress-nginx			NGINX Ingress Controller

